text=(:table valign=top:)%0a(:cellnr colspan=3 width=380 bgcolor=#005826 align=center:)%0a!!%25white%25The Sublime Conductor of Nightmare and Fancy a.k.a. The Director%25white%25%0a(:cellnr rowspan=20 width=400 align=center:) http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/silhouette.png%0a(:cellnr width=340 colspan=2 align=center:)%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/ctl/headers/ctl_s.png%0a(:cellnr width=130 align=left:)'''Age:'''%0a(:cell width=210:) ??%0a(:cellnr width=130 align=left:)'''Apparent Age:'''%0a(:cell width=210:) ??%0a(:cellnr width=130 align=left:)'''Height:'''%0a(:cell width=210:) ??%0a(:cellnr width=130 align=left:)'''Build:'''%0a(:cell width=210:) ??%0a(:cellnr width=130 align=left:)'''Profession:''' %0a(:cell width=210:) Keeper%0a(:cellnr width=130 align=left:)'''Public Effects:'''%0a(:cell width=210:) ??%0a(:cellnr width=130 align=left:)'''Run-aways'''%0a(:cell width=210:) ??%0a(:cellnr width=130 align=left:)'''Theme Music:''' %0a(:cell width=210:) ??%0a(:cellnr width=130 align=left:)'''Frailty:'''%0a(:cell width=210:) Cannot abide improvisation%0a(:tableend:)%0a%0a%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/ctl/headers/ctl_d.png%0a%0aThe Conductor is a tall, bony man with a thick handlebar mustache beneath a beaked nose and a mad look in his eyes as he twists it. His fashion seems taken, most often, from the Golden Age of Hollywood, and his accoutrements, hat, loudspeaker, and gentleman's cane) enforce his image as a stereotypical movie director of the period. His dark hair is slicked back when not hidden beneath the hat, and his fingers are often stained with ink and blood - he looks almost human until you look into his chaotic eyes and see a hundred vistas of Heaven and a thousand views of Hell in their depths. On occasion he will be seen in some other garb - from a Shakespearean ensemble of classic theater to the sharp-pressed suit, shades, and cell-phone of the modern media mogul - but he seems to prefer the accoutrements of the Golden Age.%0a%0a'''Personality'''%0a%0aThe Director is an artiste, a genius in his own mind if not in reality. His great obsession seems to be film and theater in all their permutations, and though he seems initially almost a harmless kook it soon becomes terrifyingly clear he believes in fuly-enforced method acting, and considers his "talent" less compassionately than even most other Gentry; his favor is mercurial at best, and his taste in artistic expression tends to lean toward 'carnal, dark, and bloody things.' Great historical epics, grindhouse horror, sordid pornographic works to beggar the worst deprevities of the medium in mortal imaginings - all of these and more he dabbles with, and to linger too long in the Conductor's sway is to lose oneself utterly in the role he demands -or to be given a far worse one: someone has to play the murder victim or the imprisoned torture-slave of the mad scientist, after all.%0a%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/ctl/headers/ctl_h.png%0a%25rframe%25 http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/silhouette.png%0a'''Domain'''%0aThe Backlot is a twisted nightmare parody of a mortal movie studio with chaotic anarchonisms from all ages fused together in eerily beautiful madcap combinations. The bunkhouses are of the Golden Age, a great theatrical playhouse from the Victorian era rises from its center to serve as the Conductor's lair and private cinema, and a countless, seemingly-endless parade of any set from the moon to a battlefield to an eeriily-accurate version of nearly any city on Earth and more can be found there, some of them violating all laws of sense in ways that seem strange even for Arcadia - step onto one set and all color washes from you and turns the world to greys and blacks, and another further down does the same but also robs one of all sound. The worst ones seem to be a perfect version of the Thorns that surround various sets of the major Cities of film history; more than one damned soul has spent days beleiving themselves escaped and free of the Keeper only to hear the clap of wood and the shout of 'Cut!'%0a%0a'''Seemings/Kiths'''%0aAlmost any kith or seeming can be found in thrall to the Conductor, but Fairest and Wizened tend to be most common. Fairest are obviously the primary 'Talent' for the mad Director, and Wizened of all sorts are needed to craft and maintain the sets, provide catering, and most horrifyingly of all, work in the 'costume shop' to twist new 'talent' into their roles or 'improve' their looks through twisted fae equivalents of plastic surgery. Darklings are often his spies and hsi villains, and Ogres act as set security; beasts and elementals of all sorts can be characters or set dressing alike.%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/ctl/headers/ctl_rph.png%0a'''RP Hook:'''%0aBlah blah blah blah...%0a%0a'''RP Hook:'''%0aBlah blah blah blah...%0a%0a'''Follow the Script!''' (Frailty)%0aThe Conductor's greatest weakness is that he cannot abide improvisation - as mad and horrible as his works may be, they are each scripted with insane detail and when he arrives on 'set' he will not deviate an inch from his Script, no more than he will tolerate the Talent doing so. Lost who learn of this have, more than once, found ways to thwart his security and pencil in their own additions a midst his own mad corrections - to improve their lot and rank, or even be freed by the Conductor back to the mortal world.%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/ctl/headers/ctl_q.png%0a%0a%0a[[%3c%3c]]%0a%0a(:include CityBook.ChangelingNavigationBar:)
