reys and blacks, and another further down does the same but also robs one of all sound. The worst ones seem to be a perfect version of the Thorns that surround various sets of the major Cities of film history; more than one damned soul has spent days beleiving themselves escaped and free of the Keeper only to hear the clap of wood and the shout of 'Cut!'%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Seemings/Kiths'''%0a%3c Almost any kith or seeming can be found in thrall to the Conductor, but Fairest and Wizened tend to be most common. Fairest are obviously the primary 'Talent' for the mad Director, and Wizened of all sorts are needed to craft and maintain the sets, provide catering, and most horrifyingly of all, work in the 'costume shop' to twist new 'talent' into their roles or 'improve' their looks through twisted fae equivalents of plastic surgery. Darklings are often his spies and hsi villains, and Ogres act as set security; beasts and elementals of all sorts can be characters or set dressing alike.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c %0a%3c http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/ctl/headers/ctl_rph.png%0a%3c '''RP Hook:'''%0a%3c Blah blah blah blah...%0a%3c %0a%3c '''RP Hook:'''%0a%3c Blah blah blah blah...%0a%3c %0a%3c '''Follow the Script!''' (Frailty)%0a%3c The Conductor's greatest weakness is that he cannot abide improvisation - as mad and horrible as his works may be, they are each scripted with insane detail and when he arrives on 'set' he will not deviate an inch from his Script, no more than he will tolerate the Talent doing so. Lost who learn of this have, more than once, found ways to thwart his security and pencil in their own additions a midst his own mad corrections - to improve their lot and rank, or even be freed by the Conductor back to the mortal world.%0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c %0a%3c http://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/ctl/headers/ctl_q.png%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[%3c%3c]]%0a%3c %0a%3c (:include CityBook.ChangelingNavigationBar:)%0a\ No newline at end of 